place.name: Fuji Tempura Idaten
place.description: Idaten is a casual tempura restaurant near Kawaguchiko Station. One of the reasons Idaten has been supported is the chef in action. We have an ozasiki (Japanese style) table, 3 normal tables, and about 20 counter seats, and if you get a counter seat, you are able to see the cooking in action right in front of you. Not only seeing cooking but you can also enjoy the smell and the sound of tempura while you are waiting. Many customers (especially people from other countries) already know this information before they come to us, so they prefer to sit at the counter and have some fun seeing and learning how to cook good tempura. Not many tempura restaurants in Japan cook in front of customers, so you can enjoy a great experience with us.
